Kenya Airports Authority has temporarily closed air-side access to the Jetways facility at the JKIA. The step was taken on Tuesday to allow investigations into claims of illegal and irregular activities in a premises operated by Jetways Aviation. In a statement to newsrooms, Corporate Communications Manager Angela Tilitei said: "We in KAA take safety and security seriously and wish to assure the public that we take all the concerns with the importance they deserve." Tilitei did not give details but said their security agents had been alerted about the activities. Click here for the latest political news   